Ask HN: What are the best public-code searching web apps today?
text:
You can do a global code search in Github.com or in your search engine (Google, DuckDuckGo, Bing, whatever). There are some language specific systems like Hoogle [0]. Maybe SourceGraph's global search engine [1] is ok too I have only tried their project-specific views.

What is the best hosted/free web app out there today that you use to do searches on code across one or multiple projects?

[0] https://hoogle.haskell.org/

[1] https://sourcegraph.com/search

title: 15 year old looking for internship at SpaceX
text:
Anyone know of anyone who works at SpaceX?

It’s my nephew’s dream and passion to work there. I don’t think he needs to wait until he’s an adult to make his dreams come true. He’s 15 but he is mature and can add some value to SpaceX.

SpaceX might already be hosting contests for youth and he could pitch SpaceX for an internship to help them host their youth events. Event contests aren’t anything new. Companies do it all the time.

He’d want to work part-time remote as an intern. Thanks in advance for any help you can give!
